calhost:8080/","height":256},"id":"LhS98sQxaB4x","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123772752,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":298,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"a718dd80-edc1-44ee-edc1-bda049bd0c89"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x200 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["##magnitudes\n","\n","it the measure of how bright an object is **(bigger number = dimmer object)**\n","\n","SDSS measures with five diffiernt color filters.\n","  \n","  -Ultra Violet\n","\n","  -blue-green\n","\n","  -Red\n","\n","  -Near-Inrared\n","\n","  -Infrared\n","\n","\n","  in our graphs the x-axis is the magnitude and the y-axis is the count of the galaxies, meaning the number of galaxies that have that magnitude.\n","  \n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"tvZXrzVviQuK"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20, 4))\n","for ax, band in zip(axes, ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z']):\n","    ax.hist(df_gal[band], bins=60)\n","    ax.set_title(f'{band}-band magnitude')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":334},"id":"3N-WJYz-hJZ2","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123773617,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":863,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"41b009c5-597a-4516-c304-68c96947558d"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x400 with 5 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["this is a scatter plot to visualize the relationship between each feautre and redshift. there is a big spread (galaxies of the same redshift in hugely diffierent magnitudes). but if we combine all of this we can get a strong non-linear relastionship.\n"],"metadata":{"id":"SCXpnO_cUVHw"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20, 4))\n","for ax, band in zip(axes, ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z']):\n","    ax.scatter(df_gal[band], df_gal['redshift'], s=1, alpha=0.3)\n","    ax.set_xlabel(f'{band} magnitude')\n","    ax.set_ylabel('redshift')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":334},"id":"dAQ1q7mwI_iy","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123774406,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":783,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"e8d65cb7-084d-43c0-e92a-62277d1581f2"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x400 with 5 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["restyled so its less of a blob"],"metadata":{"id":"QPdw3lmp0zFu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from matplotlib.colors import LogNorm\n","\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 5, figsize=(20, 4), sharey=True)\n","\n","bands = ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z']\n","hb = None\n","\n","for ax, band in zip(axes, bands):\n","    hb = ax.hexbin(\n","        df_gal[band],\n","        df_gal['redshift'],\n","        gridsize=60,\n","        cmap='viridis',\n","        mincnt=1,\n","        norm=LogNorm(),\n","    )\n","    ax.set_xlabel(f'{band} magnitude')\n","    ax.set_title(band)\n","\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('redshift')\n","\n","# Shared colorbar on the right\n","fig.subplots_adjust(right=0.92)\n","cbar_ax = fig.add_axes([0.93, 0.15, 0.012, 0.7])\n","cb = fig.colorbar(hb, cax=cbar_ax)\n","cb.set_label('galaxies per hex')\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":378},"id":"9IBpixxr01Xl","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123775062,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":653,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"62796d1c-0521-4233-be9b-a8389631a3a8"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x400 with 6 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["this is the correlaion matrix between redshift and color features. the u band has the weakest link between other colors and the weakest link with redshift\n","\n","the r band has the strongest corr with redshift\n","\n","we will discuss the pearson correlaion of our features in more detail later."],"metadata":{"id":"u-uVwSDcYJVH"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"c-a51vYsUH5s"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["#Section 2 - Feature engineering; Colors\n","\n","color is the difference between two magnitudes.\n","\n","e.g. u_g = u - g\n","\n","its tells us how much \"redder\" (older) a galaxy looks betwwen two filters\n","\n","why do we need colors if we already have the magnitudes?\n","\n","imagine an object that is furthur away but is bright. and another object that is closer, but dim. they both have the same magnitude.\n","\n","if we **subtract** two magnitudes the overall brightness gets cancelled out. and leaves the shape of the specturm (redder or bluier) which is what gives us information about the behavior of a particalor object.\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"4qjauQoflntK"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["df_gal['u_g'] = df_gal['u'] - df_gal['g']\n","df_gal['g_r'] = df_gal['g'] - df_gal['r']\n","df_gal['r_i'] = df_gal['r'] - df_gal['i']\n","df_gal['i_z'] = df_gal['i'] - df_gal['z']"],"metadata":{"id":"JPmSCAmOupui"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["we only compute 4 adjacent colors (u_g, g_r, r_i, i_z)\n","\n","non-adjacent colors like u_r are just sums of adjacent ones (u_r = u_g + g_r). they add no useful information.\n","\n","**clarification**\n","\n","adjacent colors mean they use filters next to each other in the specturm\n","\n","for example ultra violet - blue."],"metadata":{"id":"yB2JpMsouqoL"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["![](https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=11OJ8Wr_HPFd9fj32w8u1HfFL74eFXztx)\n"],"metadata":{"id":"a4dqb8R110ma"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(20, 4))\n","for ax, color in zip(axes, ['u_g', 'g_r', 'r_i', 'i_z']):\n","    ax.scatter(df_gal[color], df_gal['redshift'], s=1, alpha=0.3)\n","    ax.set_xlabel(f'{color} color')\n","    ax.set_ylabel('redshift')\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":334},"id":"4JKQg1xUYynl","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123775694,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":615,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"8cacac95-b2f9-42c7-f8aa-d93ad3af2892"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x400 with 4 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["when we compare our features aganist redshift we see there are a lot of outliers. lets deal with them"],"metadata":{"id":"_kkINQ0N3kje"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["for c in ['u_g', 'g_r', 'r_i', 'i_z']:\n","    n_extreme = ((df_gal[c] < -5) | (df_gal[c] > 5)).sum()\n","    print(f\"{c}: {n_extreme} outliers\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"FdB2aRTYjwgP","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123775708,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":12,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"328eec43-f230-45d3-e659-63b2ee0bed62"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["u_g: 776 outliers\n","g_r: 32 outliers\n","r_i: 25 outliers\n","i_z: 26 outliers\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["before = len(df_gal)\n","for c in ['u_g', 'g_r', 'r_i', 'i_z']:\n","    df_gal = df_gal[(df_gal[c] >= -5) & (df_gal[c] <= 5)]\n","after = len(df_gal)\n","print(f\"Removed {before - after} galaxies with extreme color values\")\n","print(f\"Clean sample size: {after}\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7DtNCgBskI9h","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123775713,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"4fa66285-f21e-423a-a08b-6cc8127411a9"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Removed 832 galaxies with extreme color values\n","Clean sample size: 57241\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["graph again"],"metadata":{"id":"DYr_CN5A3znj"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","from matplotlib.colors import LogNorm\n","\n","fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(20, 4), sharey=True)\n","\n","colors = ['u_g', 'g_r', 'r_i', 'i_z']\n","hb = None\n","\n","for ax, color in zip(axes, colors):\n","    hb = ax.hexbin(\n","        df_gal[color],\n","        df_gal['redshift'],\n","        gridsize=60,\n","        cmap='viridis',\n","        mincnt=1,\n","        norm=LogNorm(),\n","    )\n","    ax.set_xlabel(f'{color} color')\n","    ax.set_title(color)\n","\n","axes[0].set_ylabel('redshift')\n","\n","# Shared colorbar on the right, like the reference figure\n","fig.subplots_adjust(right=0.92)\n","cbar_ax = fig.add_axes([0.93, 0.15, 0.012, 0.7])\n","cb = fig.colorbar(hb, cax=cbar_ax)\n","cb.set_label('galaxies per hex')\n","\n","\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":378},"id":"XqT4YN4NkRuO","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123776414,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":686,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"a4eeedde-c7d5-4181-d87e-2080b27c9858"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 2000x400 with 5 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Although it might seem we still have noise and outliers in our data, it is not the case. What we removed previously were objects that had physically impossible attributes (magnitudes can't be too different >5 since they are essentially correlative; if it's too large, it means measurement is bad).\n","\n","What we have now are more or less objects that don't defy the laws of physics. if we exlude them we deny our model data on rare object types (very blue starburst galaxies for examble)"],"metadata":{"id":"nQkH01fc4ux8"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["### correlation matrix\n","\n","\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"j_4BZX5Y-p8w"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["features = ['u', 'g', 'r', 'i', 'z', 'u_g', 'g_r', 'r_i', 'i_z', 'redshift']\n","corr = df_gal[features].corr()\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))\n","sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm', center=0, fmt='.2f')\n","plt.title('Correlation matrix with color features')\n","\n","\n","\"\"\"plt.savefig(\"figure.pdf\", format=\"pdf\", bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n","from google.colab import files\n","files.download(\"figure.pdf\")\"\"\"\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":699},"id":"FQXajAnOY8Rv","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1777123777725,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":1309,"user":{"displayName":"AHMAD SAUD A ALQUSAIYER","userId":"03385664461315125153"}},"outputId":"5cebead1-bbfd-47c9-d17b-c932e7bb94cc"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"],"application/javascript":["\n","    async function download(id, filename, size) {\n","      if (!google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed) {\n","        return;\n","      }\n","      const div = document.createElement('div');\n","      const label = document.createElement('label');\n","      label.textContent = `Downloading \"${filename}\": `;\n","      div.appendChild(label);\n","      const progress = document.createElement('progress');\n","      progress.max = size;\n","      div.appendChild(progress);\n","      document.body.appendChild(div);\n","\n","      const buffers = [];\n","      let downloaded = 0;\n","\n","      const channel = await google.colab.kernel.comms.open(id);\n","      // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n","      channel.send({})\n","\n","      for await (const message of channel.messages) {\n","        // Send a message to notify the kernel that we're ready.\n","        channel.send({})\n","        if (message.buffers) {\n","          for (const buffer of message.buffers) {\n","            buffers.push(buffer);\n","            downloaded += buffer.byteLength;\n","            progress.value = downloaded;\n","          }\n","        }\n","      }\n","      const blob = new Blob(buffers, {type: 'application/binary'});\n","      const a = document.createElement('a');\n","      a.href = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n","      a.download = filename;\n","      div.appendChild(a);\n","      a.click();\n","      div.remove();\n","    }\n","  "]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<IPython.core.display.Javascript object>"],"application/javascript":["download(\"download_ac2cd959-a528-46c3-822c-636ba6fa7b9f\", \"figure.pdf\", 18822)"]},"metadata":{}},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x800 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["if we look at the bottom row (corr with redshift) we see that raw magnitudes correlate much better than colors do. it would seem that it contracdicts what we have setup so far.\n","\n","but this is a bit misleading, pearson correlation measures linear relationships. if we note the previvous graph we see that the color-redshift scatter plots are *largely* S shaped. linear correlation cant really capture the predicitive power of such relationship. but tree-based models and neural networks do.\n","\n","we can also note that the magnitudes are heavily correlated with each other. this is multicollinearity (if a galaxy is bright in one band it its going to be bright in others, its just light in the end). this is bad for linear models.\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"dn-CYC-uA2Bi"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["\n","\n","---\n","\n","\n","\n","---\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"zwmgnqk4E90F"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["in the next notebook we will create baselines for our project and compare them with a releavnt paper"],"metadata":{"id":"U5m7JsNXZVjJ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#saving our dataframe\n","#from google.colab import drive\n","#drive.mount('/content/drive')\n","#df_gal.to_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/files/cs465/Project/data/sdssDF.csv', index=False)\n","\n","#(commented we dont run it everytime)"],"metadata":{"id":"lsD97z6rZnio"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]}]}